Document: RetargetModifier3D
Path: godot/classes/class_retargetmodifier3d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the RetargetModifier3D class, which controls how bone transforms are retargeted between skeletons.

Property Descriptions
enable (bitfield[TransformFlag]): Flags to control the process of the transform elements individually when use_global_pose is disabled. Default: 7.
Method: set_enable_flags(value: bitfield[TransformFlag])
Method: get_enable_flags() → bitfield[TransformFlag]

profile (SkeletonProfile): SkeletonProfile for retargeting bones with names matching the bone list.
Method: set_profile(value: SkeletonProfile)
Method: get_profile() → SkeletonProfile

use_global_pose (bool): If false, in case the target skeleton has fewer bones than the source skeleton, the source bone parent's transform will be ignored. Instead, it is possible to retarget between models with different body shapes, and position, rotation, and scale can be retargeted separately. If true, retargeting is performed taking into account global pose. In case the target skeleton has fewer bones than the source skeleton, the source bone parent's transform is taken into account. However, bone length between skeletons must match exactly, if not, the bones will be forced to expand or shrink. This is useful for using dummy bone with length 0 to match postures when retargeting between models with different number of bones. Default: false.
Method: set_use_global_pose(value: bool)
Method: is_using_global_pose() → bool
